{"atom_id": "md_dmFT_assn_a007", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/FT/assumptions.md", "line_start": 13, "line_end": 13, "verbatim": "1. The name of a QRS instrument is described under the variable --CAT in the relevant QRS domain (i.e., FT, QS, RS), and may be either abbreviations or longer names. For example, \"ADAS-COG\", \"BPI SHORT FORM\", and \"APACHE II\" are all --CATs which are shortened names for the instruments they represent, whereas \"4 STAIR ASCEND\" is the FTCAT for the instrument of the same name. Sponsors should always reference CDISC Controlled Terminology.", "parent_section": "§FT [FT — Assumptions]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T12:00:00Z"}}
